            'Financial Implications of Errors in Filing Form 3 and Form 4: Mistakes in filing official forms can lead to fines and legal issues. Late filing of Form 3 or Form 4 attracts penalties.Incorrect information can result in rejection or queries from the ROC.Fixing errors often means extra legal costs and more paperwork.Amendments may also require legal support, affidavits, and partner resolutions, adding to overall compliance costs. These forms must be filed within 30 days to stay compliant.',
